!! Upgrading mind-elixir

# Download `MindElixir.iife.js` and `MindElixir.css` from `https://unpkg.com/mind-elixir@<new-version>/dist/`.
# Replace `lib/mind-elixir.umd.js` (the IIFE) — preserve the CommonJS trailer at the bottom:
```
;if(typeof module !== "undefined" && module.exports){module.exports=MindElixir;}
```
# Replace `lib/mind-elixir.css`.
# Bump `version` in `plugin.info`. Add a `changelog.tid` entry.
# Restart TiddlyWiki (library is a JS module).
# Smoke test: open an existing `<$mindmap>`, verify it renders and `operation` events still produce ops.

!! Adapter changes

JS edits to `adapter.js` need a restart. The widget caches the engine class at module load — restart is required even for behaviour-only changes.

!! Testing translation logic

`Engine.prototype._handleOperation` is the translation surface. To unit-test:

```
var Engine = require("$:/plugins/rimir/mindmap-elixir/adapter.js");
var e = new Engine($tw.wiki);
var captured = [];
e.on("op", function (op) { captured.push(op); });
e.lastMdom = { root: { id: "r", children: [{ id: "a" }] } };
e._handleOperation({ name: "finishEdit", obj: { id: "a", topic: "New A" } });
// expect captured = [{ op: "rename", id: "a", label: "New A" }]
```

!! Adding plugin-install support (future)

To allow users to install mind-elixir plugins like `nodeMenu` or `nodeMenuNeo`, extend `Engine.prototype.init` to read a `plugins` array from `options` and call `this.me.install(...)` for each. Document the expected shape in `settings.tid`.

